author: Dailymail.Com Reporter
title: Fans rush to support Adele online after Grammys flub | Daily Mail Online
text: 'You get every do over you ever need': Ellen DeGeneres leads fans rushing to support Adele online after songstress flubbed her George Michael tribute and asked the Grammys to start again Millions watching Grammys Sunday were shocked when Adele stopped the show The songstress was singing 'Fast Love' as a tribute to pop icon George Michael In first verse, the singer realized she hadn't censored herself and asked for re-do Ellen DeGeneres led fans who rushed to support the 28-year-old artist Nikki Minaj also gave her props on Instagram, calling her do-over a 'boss' move Fans poured out support for her online, in addition to some hilarious memes Published: 05:48 GMT, 13 February 2017 | Updated: 07:04 GMT, 13 February 2017 211 shares
